name: BENE_SK
comment: A UNIQUE NUMBER ASSIGNED BY THE ENROLLMENT DATA BASE (EDB) TO EACH EDB RECORD TO IDENTIFY A BENEFICIARY.

name: BENE_LIS_EFCTV_CD
comment: SWITCH INDICATING THAT THIS RECORD IS THE CURRENT EFFECTIVE LOW INCOME SUBSIDY (LIS) DETERMINATION RECORD.

name: SRC_ID_SK
comment: IDENTIFIER OF SOURCE SYSTEM / USERS RELATED TO AUDITS, STARTING AND ENDING PERIODS.

name: BENE_LIS_COPMT_LVL_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE GENERIC LEVEL USED TO COMPUTE THE LOW INCOME SUBSIDY (LIS) CO-PAYMENT AMOUNT. THIS GENERIC LEVEL TRANSLATES TO A SPECIFIC NUMERIC VALUE THAT WILL BE USED IN THE COMPUTATION.    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_LIS_COPMT_LVL_CD

name: BENE_LIS_APL_RSLT_CD
comment: A CODE INDICATING THE RESULT OF AN APPEAL FILED BY A BENEFICIARY FOR LOW INCOME SUBSIDY (LIS).    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_LIS_APL_RSLT_CD

name: BENE_LIS_APRVL_CD
comment: IDENTIFIES WHETHER THE APPLICATION FOR SUBSIDY WAS APPROVED OR NOT APPROVED.

name: BENE_LIS_CHG_CD
comment: A CODE INDICATING IF A CHANGE WAS MADE TO A PREVIOUS LOW INCOME SUBSIDY (LIS) DETERMINATION.    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_LIS_CHG_CD

name: BENE_LIS_CNCL_CD
comment: A CODE INDICATING IF A PREVIOUS SUBMISSION FOR LOW INCOME SUBSIDY (LIS) DETERMINATION SHOULD BE CANCELLED.    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_LIS_CNCL_CD

name: BENE_LIS_INCM_DTRMNTN_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING IF THE INCOME DETERMINATION FOR A LOW INCOME SUBSIDY (LIS) BENEFICIARY WAS BASED ON AN INDIVIDUAL OR A COUPLE.    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_LIS_INCM_DTRMNTN_CD

name: BENE_LIS_RSRC_LVL_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE AMOUNT OF A BENEFICIARYS FINANCIAL ASSETS THAT ARE USED IN THE DETERMINATION OF SUBSIDY ELIGIBILITY AND COPAYMENT AMOUNTS.    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_LIS_RSRC_LVL_CD

name: BENE_LIS_PTD_PRM_PCT
comment: IDENTIFIES THE PORTION OF THE PART D PREMIUM SUBSIDIZED, BASED ON A SLIDING SCALE LINKED TO THE FEDERAL POVERTY LEVEL (FPL) PERCENTAGE. IF THE PERSON IS UNDER 135% FPL THE PREMIUM SUBSIDY PERCENT WILL BE 100%.  IF THE PERSON IS 136-140% FPL THE PREMIUM SUBSIDY PERCENT WILL BE 75%.    IF THE PERSON IS 141-145% FPL THE PREMIUM SUBSIDY WILL BE 50%.  IF THE PERSON IS 146-149% FPL THE PREMIUM SUBSIDY WILL BE 25%.

name: BENE_LIS_FPL_PCT
comment: FOR THOSE INDIVIDUALS WHO APPLY FOR THE LOW INCOME SUBSIDY, IDENTIFIES THE SPECIFIC PERCENT OF FEDERAL POVERTY LEVEL (FPL).

name: BENE_LIS_APLCTN_DT
comment: SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA) DATE OF THE LOW INCOME SUBSIDY APPLICATION.

name: BENE_LIS_PTD_APRVL_DT
comment: DATE THAT THE PART D LOW INCOME SUBSIDY WAS APPROVED.

name: SRC_AUDT_ID_SK
comment: SOURCE OF THE AUDITED INFORMATION.

name: META_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND A 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT INITIALLY LOADED A ROW IN THE IDR. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: META_LAST_UPDT_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND A 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT INITIALLY LOADED A ROW IN THE IDR. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: META_SRC_SK
comment: A UNIQUE NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) USED TO IDENTIFY THE SPECIFIC SOURCE OF THE DATA WHEN A ROW IS LOADED INTO THE IDR.    REFERENCE TABLE: V2_MDCR_META_DCTNRY_SRC

name: META_SRC_ID
comment: UNIQUE IDENTIFIER OF A SOURCE.

name: BENE_RNG_BGN_DT
comment: DATE THAT THE LOW INCOME SUBSIDY WILL BEGIN.

name: BENE_RNG_END_DT
comment: DATE THAT THE LOW INCOME SUBSIDY WILL END.

name: IDR_TRANS_OBSLT_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) WHEN A RECORD WAS LAST KNOWN TO BE PRESENT IN THE SOURCE. THE CURRENT VERSION OF A RECORD WILL BE SET TO 12/31/9999 00:00:00.

name: IDR_LTST_TRANS_FLG
comment: AN INDICATOR ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) THAT IDENTIFIES WHICH TRANSACTION RECORD, BASED ON PRIMARY KEY, IS CONSIDERED TO REPRESENT THE MOST RECENT RECORD RECEIVED FROM THE SOURCE.    Y = LATEST VERSION OF THE RECORD  N = PREVIOUS VERSION OF THE RECORD

name: META_SRC_PRCSG_ID
comment: A VALUE ASSIGNED BASED ON A BATCH IDENTIFICATION IN ORDER TO TRACE IT BACK TO ITS ORIGINAL SOURCE. IT WILL ONLY BE POPULATED WHEN A RECORD IS INSERTED.

name: META_LTST_SRC_PRCSG_ID
comment: A VALUE ASSIGNED BASED ON A BATCH IDENTIFICATION IN ORDER TO TRACE IT BACK TO ITS ORIGINAL SOURCE. IT WILL ONLY BE POPULATED WHEN A RECORD IS SUBSEQUENTLY UPDATED.

name: IDR_INSRT_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) WHILE PERFORMING AN INSERT OPERATION.

name: IDR_UPDT_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) WHEN UPDATES ARE MADE TO ANY NON-PRIMARY KEY COLUMN.
